HEADWORD: Lactobutyrometer
<hw>Lac`to*bu`ty*rom"e*ter</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>lac</ets>, <ets>lactis</ets>, milk + E.
<ets>butyrometer</ets>.]</ety> <def>An instrument for determining the
amount of butter fat contained in a given sample of milk.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

